The paper deals with the synthesis of shared control protocols for robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of inverse reinforcement learning and randomized strategies suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The involvement of a human in the control loop and the consideration of imperfect interfaces indicate a potential connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of quasiconvex programming suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
